BUSINESS mogul and Chairman Casiva Group of Companies, Alhaji Nasiru Dano, has donated two Argentine ponies (horses) to the Nigerian Navy Polo team. He said the gesture is to encourage the Navy team for their outstanding performance and the game of polo in the country in general.   Nketiah pens new five-year deal at Arsenal     BetKing empowers 100 entrepreneurs     Aribo reaffirms Rangers’ stay   While presenting the ponies to the Chief of Naval Staff, Vice Admiral Awwal Zubairu Gambo, the donor, maintained: “The Navy team is the fastest-growing polo team today in Nigeria. In less than a year, they have won the Chief of Naval Staff Vice Adm. Awwal Gambo Conference, which took place in Kano State, and in Abuja, they did marvelously well by clinching the trophies. “They also won the Theophilus Danjuma’s Polo Tournament in Port Harcourt as well as the 50th Anniversary of the Nigerian Army Polo competition. In Lagos during the Lagos State Polo Tournament, they did very well. We at Casiva Ltd., want the team to do more because we have seen their commitment. of the CNS. In less than one year, what NN has done is a pointer to the fact that they are really making the military and the country proud.